@node Introduction
@chapter Introduction
@cindex introduction
@cindex overview

Codebud is a local, CPU-friendly coding agent.  You describe a task in
plain English; Codebud asks a locally-running language model to produce a
step-by-step plan, validates it against a safety policy, executes each step
using built-in tools (file I/O, shell commands, unified-diff patching,
web search, embeddings), and records what happened in a persistent memory
timeline.  No data leaves your machine.

